🌐 Computer Networks
1️⃣ HTTP Deep (Methods + Status Codes) 🔥
Simple Idea

HTTP defines how client (browser) communicates with server

Mental Model (Restaurant 🍽️)
You (client) → order food
Waiter (HTTP) → takes request
Kitchen (server) → prepares response
HTTP Methods
Method	Meaning
GET	Fetch data
POST	Send data
PUT	Update data
DELETE	Remove data
Status Codes
Code	Meaning
200	OK
404	Not Found
500	Server Error
Why It Works

Standard communication → all websites work consistently.

Memory Trick 🧠

GET = take
POST = send

2️⃣ Web Caching
Simple Idea

Stores frequently accessed data to reduce loading time.

Mental Model

You save notes locally instead of downloading every time.

Types
Browser cache
Proxy cache
CDN cache
Why It Works
faster loading
reduces server load
Memory Trick

Cache = Save for later use

3️⃣ Proxy vs Gateway
Proxy

Acts as middleman for client

Gateway

Acts as middleman for server

Mental Model

Proxy → your assistant talking to others
Gateway → server’s assistant

Why It Works

Helps in:

security
filtering
protocol conversion
Memory Trick

Proxy = client side
Gateway = server side

4️⃣ VPN (Virtual Private Network)
Simple Idea

Creates a secure private connection over internet.

Mental Model 🔒

Like using a secret tunnel to send data.

Why It Works
encrypts data
hides IP
increases privacy
Real Example

Access blocked websites using VPN.

Memory Trick

VPN = private tunnel

🌍 Social Networks
5️⃣ Network Clustering
Simple Idea

Formation of tight groups inside network.

Mental Model

Friend groups in college:

close-knit circles
Why It Works

People with similar interests cluster together.

Memory Trick

Cluster = group of close nodes

6️⃣ Triadic Closure
Simple Idea

If A knows B and B knows C → A likely knows C.

Mental Model

Your friend introduces you to their friend.

Why It Works

Trust spreads through connections.

Memory Trick

Friend of friend → becomes friend

7️⃣ Social Influence Models
Simple Idea

People change behavior based on others.

Mental Model

If many friends start gym → you also start.

Why It Works

Humans follow trends.

Memory Trick

Influence = behavior change

8️⃣ Network Visualization
Simple Idea

Graphical representation of network.

Mental Model

Like drawing a map of connections.

Why It Matters

Helps analyze:

patterns
communities
influence
Memory Trick

Visualization = see the network

🎯 10 Most Asked Computer Network Interview Questions
1️⃣ What is HTTP?

Protocol for communication between client and server.

2️⃣ What are HTTP methods?

GET, POST, PUT, DELETE.

3️⃣ What is status code 404?

Page not found.

4️⃣ What is web caching?

Storing data for faster access.

5️⃣ What is a proxy server?

Client-side intermediary.

6️⃣ What is a gateway?

Server-side intermediary.

7️⃣ What is VPN?

Secure private network over internet.

8️⃣ What is HTTPS?

Secure version of HTTP.

9️⃣ What is REST API?

Web service using HTTP methods.

🔟 Difference between HTTP and HTTPS?

HTTP → not secure
HTTPS → encrypted

